Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.02,0:00:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A racing second hand,\Ntiny shooting stars!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.81,0:00:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan's logic is good medicine\Nfor hearts tired by modern society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.40,0:00:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's case is a Western legend!\NDon't put much stake in theories!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.94,0:00:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single\Ntruth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.60,0:00:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.61,0:00:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.09,0:02:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dracula Manor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.01,0:02:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Most of Mr. Dorakura's\Nnovels are centered around vampires,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.43,0:02:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he's earned the\Nnickname "Mr. Dracula."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.44,0:02:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why it's\Ncalled Dracula Manor?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.48,0:02:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Dorakura Daisuke a famous writer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.78,0:02:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the most popular writer in\Nthe Japan Horror Novel Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.82,0:02:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's even started to branch\Nout into heroic fantasy novels,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.54,0:02:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and is gaining female fans, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.16,0:02:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure know a lot about him, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.04,0:02:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do! I am a\Nbrilliant detective, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.84,0:02:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.67,0:02:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Horror Times Monthly--\NSpecial Dorakura Daisuke Issue!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.01,0:02:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, a cheat sheet, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.89,0:02:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.85,0:02:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.90,0:02:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Dracula Manor?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.90,0:03:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Dracula Manor Murder Case (Part 1)."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.22,0:03:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.68,0:03:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.18,0:03:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming all this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.10,0:03:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.64,0:03:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Tadokoro, I'm studying\Nunder Dorakura-{\i1}sensei{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.11,0:03:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been waiting for you.\NCome this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.66,0:03:51.29,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura Etsuko (30) Dorakura Daisuke's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.78,0:03:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.29,0:03:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a beautiful woman!\NI'm jealous!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.21,0:03:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.50,0:03:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.76,0:04:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old mansions certainly\Nhave a unique feel to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.93,0:04:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get a chill down\Nmy spine for some reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.60,0:04:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.10,0:04:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.61,0:04:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Might you be Mori\NKogoro-{\i1}san{\i0}, the detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.07,0:04:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:28.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it! It's an honor to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.40,0:04:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Doi, editor in chief for\NDaigakkan's Horror Times Monthly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.87,0:04:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know that magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.42,0:04:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, so you're the famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.96,0:04:48.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura Shuichi (33) NKU Folklore Researcher
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.13,0:04:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Hamura Shuichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.34,0:04:48.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a folklore researcher\Nat North Kanto University.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.47,0:04:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What sort of research do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.14,0:04:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mainly... vampire legends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.90,0:05:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh. That's interesting research...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.32,0:05:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, where's Mr. Dorakura?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.61,0:05:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in the study, writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.61,0:05:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's... a study room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.87,0:05:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A black-out curtain...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.36,0:05:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a movie...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.86,0:05:46.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Kogoro-{\i1}san{\i0}, I take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.32,0:05:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to Dracula Manor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.37,0:05:53.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura Daisuke (50) Horror Writer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.74,0:05:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Dorakura Daisuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.67,0:06:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Octagonal rooms certainly are rare...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.22,0:06:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... do you always dress\Nup like Dracula like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By writing while cloaked in Dracula\Nattire as I play Dracula films,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.94,0:06:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought many a\Nmasterpiece into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.44,0:06:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.90,0:06:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish to hire you to investigate\Nthe behavior of my wife, Etsuko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.95,0:06:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Behavior? An affair, in other words?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.12,0:06:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.37,0:06:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to find definitive proof\Nof the affair, and the man it's with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard called me all the way out\Nhere just for some stupid affair...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.13,0:06:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am willing to pay one million yen,\Nand related expenses, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.55,0:06:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly! I gladly accept the job!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:07:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn. I didn't bring\Nany chains for the car...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No worries. You may spend\Nthe night here, in Dracula Manor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.65,0:07:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll do that, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.50,0:07:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a lovely smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.17,0:07:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's homemade rosemary tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.63,0:07:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And dinner was delicious, too!\NYou're a good cook, Tadokoro-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.89,0:07:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to him, the lady of the\Nhouse can live an easy, carefree life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.56,0:07:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm studying novel-writing here,\Nso it's only natural that I help out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.48,0:07:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great. I look forward to your\Nnew series starting next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.28,0:07:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, I must finish this\Nmonth's manuscript first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:08:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro, bring wine\Nand a movie to the study.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.46,0:08:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.\NWhat movie would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.00,0:08:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.05,0:08:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say! Ran-{\i1}san{\i0}! Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! \NWant to come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.72,0:08:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's lots of rare stuff to see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.77,0:08:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rare stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.60,0:08:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He means Dorakura-{\i1}sensei{\i0}'s\Nprized "Dracula Collection,"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,full of props and costumes\Nfrom vampire films.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.52,0:08:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go see, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.53,0:08:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.40,0:08:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.37,0:08:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His vast collection of props\Nand films are kept in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.51,0:08:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where do these stairs go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.38,0:08:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's a library in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.84,0:09:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's filled with vampire books and\Nold texts from around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.81,0:09:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Dracula Library, you could call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.98,0:09:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, a Dracula mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.19,0:09:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Dracula hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.65,0:09:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A cross sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.16,0:09:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this one'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.74,0:09:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you decided on a movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.74,0:09:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. An old British movie\Ncalled Banquet of Fresh Blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.25,0:09:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He just loves this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.63,0:09:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See that wooden stake there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.38,0:09:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was driven through the vampire's\Nheart in the last scene of this film.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.09,0:09:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In his study, he also has the\Ncross the vampire was strung up on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I smell oil paint...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.02,0:09:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd. There aren't\Nany oil paintings...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.35,0:09:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.94,0:09:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.11,0:09:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Ran-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.23,0:09:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to ask, but could you\Nmake sure all the windows are locked?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.99,0:09:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, no problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.13,0:10:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.96,0:10:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.05,0:10:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you think\Nof the Dracula Collection?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.81,0:10:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was kind of gross!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.32,0:10:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Hamura-{\i1}san{\i0}. \NDracula is just fiction, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.32,0:10:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that the Count Dracula we know
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.24,0:10:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was a monster created by\NBram Stoker in his 1897 novel, Dracula.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.08,0:10:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, there were several\Nnoblemen in medieval Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.50,0:10:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who were feared as vampires\Nbecause of the atrocities they committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.92,0:11:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura-{\i1}sensei {\i0}has collected\Nmany old documents concerning that,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.72,0:11:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which is why I visit here personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.07,0:11:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Want to play cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.37,0:11:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.58,0:11:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! Hold on while I make\Nsure everything's locked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.55,0:11:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadokoro-{\i1}san {\i0}seems really nice,\Ndoes he like horror novels, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.43,0:11:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, I'd say he's\Nprobably more into fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.85,0:11:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who introduced\Nhim to Dorakura-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.39,0:11:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He seemed to have real talent, you see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.53,0:12:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it still snowing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.69,0:12:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's stopped now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you two play cards with us, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.04,0:12:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I have a headache,\Nso I'm going to bed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.63,0:12:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'd like to browse the library\Na bit more. If you'll excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.76,0:12:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Use your 6 of Hearts already!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.52,0:12:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not gonna happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.89,0:12:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my theory was right on the mark!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.31,0:12:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.40,0:12:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you join us, Hamura-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.24,0:12:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san {\i0}is retelling his many exploits!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.12,0:12:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.20,0:12:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to use the restroom.\NI've been feeling ill since this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.46,0:12:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.25,0:13:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad. We're going to bed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.73,0:13:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do that. It's grownup time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.81,0:13:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.48,0:13:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.15,0:13:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't answer the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.49,0:13:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think maybe he dozed off?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd never do that! Late nights\Nand alcohol never affect him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.83,0:13:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.50,0:13:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei! Say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.59,0:13:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.75,0:13:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.84,0:13:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.01,0:13:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all the noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.14,0:13:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am! Your husband\Nisn't responding to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.60,0:13:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.52,0:13:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear the projector!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.44,0:14:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be! Shouldn't the\Nmovie be long over by now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.52,0:14:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go outside and\Ncall for him from the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.36,0:14:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.32,0:14:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.79,0:14:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The window's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.20,0:14:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the snow by the\Nwindow's been trampled on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.25,0:14:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.17,0:14:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura-{\i1}san{\i0}! Are you in here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.47,0:14:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.64,0:14:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.22,0:14:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.97,0:15:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the windows, but the one\Nwe entered from, are fixed in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.09,0:15:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.36,0:15:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the only door is locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.12,0:15:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rubber sealing...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.20,0:15:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be impossible to use\Nstring to lock it from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.00,0:15:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would appear the killer entered\Nand exited through that window.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.59,0:15:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}, how did\Nthe killer get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.22,0:15:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the snow in front\Nof the window was trampled...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.26,0:15:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there were no other footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.10,0:15:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Climbing up the cliff\Nwould be impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.06,0:15:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the rough waves in the lake\Nwould quickly capsize any boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.90,0:15:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, even with the window open,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:16:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this study room was\Nstill as good as locked...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.99,0:16:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did the police say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.86,0:16:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.66,0:16:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The snowstorm caused an avalanche\Nthat blocked the only road here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.16,0:16:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say they can't clear\Nthe road until at least morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.67,0:16:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn... Looks like I'll\Nhave to examine the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.46,0:16:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a vulgar murderer,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.09,0:16:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,killing him with a wooden stake,\Nas if he were Dracula...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.26,0:16:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and sticking his body\Non a cross, on top of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.52,0:16:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.02,0:16:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did the killer move the\Nprojector and light up the body?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.73,0:16:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there some reason behind it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.69,0:16:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost like the last scene\Nof Banquet of Fresh Blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.61,0:16:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Banquet of Fresh Blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.78,0:16:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the movie\NTadokoro-{\i1}san {\i0}brought him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.62,0:16:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.95,0:16:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Dorakura-{\i1}sensei{\i0}'s\Nmost beloved vampire film.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.62,0:16:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the killer set it up to look\Nlike the movie's last scene?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.96,0:17:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rigor mortis has set in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.13,0:17:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning he's probably\Nbeen dead for at least an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.84,0:17:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, the time of the murder\Nwas between 9:00 and 11:00 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.40,0:17:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a wound on the back of his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.81,0:17:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've been hit with this.\NThere's some blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.61,0:17:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.86,0:17:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was strung up and impaled with\Nthe stake after being knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.66,0:17:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}, that stake came\Nfrom the collection room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.33,0:17:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.08,0:17:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, the killer snuck in\Nand stole the stake
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.34,0:17:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after Tadokoro-{\i1}san\N{\i0}came to get the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.92,0:17:48.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, after Tadokoro-{\i1}san {\i0}delivered\Nthe movie to the study room,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.09,0:17:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the person murdered Mr. Dorakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.35,0:17:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.60,0:17:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't smell like oil paint...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.31,0:17:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But all the windows\Nwere locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.98,0:18:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's not a single\Nfootprint outside the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.11,0:18:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the killer is an insider!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.87,0:18:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mister! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.21,0:18:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The end of a twig...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.84,0:18:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's got nothin' to do with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.67,0:18:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.38,0:18:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who\Ncould've stolen the stake
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.39,0:18:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is you, who went to browse the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.72,0:18:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.69,0:18:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}, how exactly\Ndid I take the stake to the study?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.65,0:18:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would've had to pass through\Nthe living room, where you all were.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.52,0:18:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.70,0:18:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is one way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.24,0:18:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.28,0:18:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By going upstairs and\Nwalking across the corridor's roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.45,0:18:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could get to the study that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.08,0:19:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.08,0:19:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need your help!\NI already knew that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.09,0:19:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I wanted to leave, I would still\Nhave to go through the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.26,0:19:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, I couldn't have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.35,0:19:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.06,0:19:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.27,0:19:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your room is above\Nthe collection room, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.40,0:19:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, you conspired\Nwith Hamura-{\i1}san{\i0}, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.69,0:19:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you saying, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.78,0:19:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could dangle a rope to the\Ncollection room window from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.78,0:19:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura-{\i1}san {\i0}used it\Nto climb up to your room,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.29,0:19:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then traversed the corridor\Nroof to reach the study.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.54,0:19:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He then scaled the roof there\Nand set down in front of that window.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.96,0:19:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, he called out to\NMr. Dorakura to let him inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.55,0:19:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then murdered him\Nwhen he got the chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.09,0:19:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used the same course\Nin reverse to get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.14,0:19:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.14,0:19:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.89,0:20:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would Hamura-{\i1}san {\i0}and I need\Nto conspire to kill my husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.44,0:20:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Dorakura suspected\Nyou of having an affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.57,0:20:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, were you having\Nan affair with Hamura-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What makes you think we're--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.32,0:20:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Etsuko, let's not hide the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.91,0:20:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hamura-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.37,0:20:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police would find\Nout right away, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.58,0:20:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you admit it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.67,0:20:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do. But, we truly love each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.51,0:20:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Hamura-{\i1}san {\i0}is the only one I love!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.84,0:20:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never once loved Dorakura!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.76,0:20:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did you get married?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.64,0:20:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eight years ago, my father's\Nbusiness took a nosedive
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.98,0:20:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and was on the verge of bankruptcy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.36,0:20:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dorakura was an old\Nacquaintance of my father's,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.03,0:20:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and in exchange for\Nfinancing the business,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.86,0:21:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he demanded my hand in marriage\Nafter I had just graduated college!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.87,0:21:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the company went bankrupt,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.54,0:21:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so many people, and families,\Nwould be affected!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.46,0:21:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I had no choice but to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.04,0:21:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We later learned\Nthat the business' downfall
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.05,0:21:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was actually because of Dorakura's\Nbehind-the-scenes dirty work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.89,0:21:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, by the time we found out,\Nthe company was already in his name,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.10,0:21:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he threatened to destroy\Nthe company if we divorced...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.01,0:21:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's horrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.52,0:21:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.06,0:21:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Mr. Dorakura died, his wife\Nwould inherit his company...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.74,0:21:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's why you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.69,0:21:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It wasn't us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.58,0:21:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have proof that we killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.54,0:21:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. If that's how\Nyou want it, then I'll show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.17,0:21:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You left her room, climbed onto\Nthe corridor roof from this window,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.76,0:21:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and went to the study.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.51,0:22:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old guy's on the ball today!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.26,0:22:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why Hamura-{\i1}san{\i0}'s\Nfootprints are still on the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.27,0:22:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-There aren't any footprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.02,0:22:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.78,0:22:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.45,0:22:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's not a single footprint!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.36,0:22:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the corridor unusable, this roof\Nwas the only way to the study!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.95,0:22:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me the killer actually\Nflew through the air, like a vampire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.95,0:24:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the rest to me, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.71,0:24:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, I thought only Hamura-{\i1}san\N{\i0}could have taken the stake,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.13,0:24:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but actually, anyone could\Nhave stolen it from outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.68,0:24:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.01,0:24:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no footprints because\Nthe killer walked through the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.79,0:24:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Walked through the air?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.17,0:24:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan: "The Dracula\NManor Murder Case (Part 2)."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.21,0:24:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.70,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.46,0:24:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode dad displays some impressive detective skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.81,0:24:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you mean impressive sleeping skills?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.94,0:24:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
